      <article><p>You run a startup. You’ve just raised your first serious money, and need to start spending it wisely to hit your goals you promised to your investor.</p>

<p>You’re hiring developers like crazy, but going slower than ever! What’s gone wrong?</p>

<p>Your Lead Developer keeps saying “we need to build a CD/CI pipeline, so I’m going to take one developer away to focus on that, it’ll make life better in the long run”.</p>

<p>And you go “No! We need all hands on getting the next Shiny New Feature out, we have no time for whatever you just said..”</p>

<p>Sound familiar? We, as a profession, need to get better at explaining what we do in terms that a non-technical startup CEO can understand.</p>

<p>Why doesn’t the manager understand the developer? and vice versa.</p>

<p>I’m going to talk about what DevOps is, and how adopting a DevOps mindset can help you deliver better software faster with a happier team.</p>
